english:
  title: 'Spring Day: Inviting a Friend Who Does Not Come, Sent in Verse'
  author: Choi Chi-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Remembering long ago the hardships endured in Chang'an—
    how can I bear to let this spring in my homeland slip away in vain?
    Yet this morning I break my promise to walk the mountains,
    regretting the day I came to know those who chase fame and profit in the dust.
  footnotes:
    - 'Chang''an (長安): The ancient capital of China, likely referring to Choi Chi-won''s years of service in China during the Tang Dynasty'
    - The broken promise to walk the mountains represents the speaker's entanglement with worldly affairs and social obligations that prevent simple communion with nature and friends
